{"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Related","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SharedFolder","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawTemplate"],"title":"Related"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup","roleHeading":"API Collection","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide"]}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai","type":"reference"},{"text":" is an open-source self-hosted AI assistant","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that connects to Claude, GPT-4, Gemini, and other models. Running OpenClaw","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in macOS VMs with Spooktacular gives you:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Isolation","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — each instance has its own macOS environment, API keys,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and workspace. A misconfigured agent can’t affect the other.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2 instances per Mac"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Apple Silicon’s 2-VM kernel limit maps","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"perfectly to running a pair of agents (e.g., work + personal,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or production + staging).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots"}]},{"text":" — save a working OpenClaw configuration, experiment,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and roll back if something breaks.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes-managed"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — scale OpenClaw instances across a fleet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of Macs using "},{"code":"MacOSVMPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Prerequisites","text":"Prerequisites","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS 14+ on the host","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular installed ("},{"code":"brew install --cask spooktacular","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API key from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Quick-Start-Two-OpenClaw-Instances","text":"Quick Start: Two OpenClaw Instances","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"1-Create-the-first-VM","text":"1. Create the first VM","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"code":["spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"anchor":"2-Clone-for-the-second-instance","text":"2. Clone for the second instance","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"code":["spook clone openclaw-work openclaw-personal"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The clone takes ~50ms (APFS copy-on-write). Each VM gets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unique machine identifier automatically."}]},{"anchor":"3-Start-both","text":"3. Start both","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"code":["spook start openclaw-work --headless","spook start openclaw-personal --headless"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both VMs boot and run OpenClaw independently. Each listens","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on its own IP address, port 18789.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"4-Check-status","text":"4. Check status","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"code":["spook list","spook ip openclaw-work","spook ip openclaw-personal"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"anchor":"User-Data-Script-for-OpenClaw","text":"User-Data Script for OpenClaw","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a script that installs and configures OpenClaw automatically:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-openclaw.sh — installs OpenClaw in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew (if not present)","if ! command -v brew &>\/dev\/null; then","    \/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","    eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","fi","","# Install Node.js 24","brew install node@24","echo 'export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"' >> ~\/.zshrc","export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","","# Install OpenClaw","npm install -g openclaw@latest","","# Run onboard with daemon installation","# (The API key should be set via environment variable or","#  injected via the shared folder)","openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","echo \"OpenClaw installed and running on port 18789\""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For production deployments, pass the API key via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a shared folder or environment variable rather than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hardcoding it in the script."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Passing-API-Keys-Securely","text":"Passing API Keys Securely","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a shared folder to deliver configuration without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"embedding secrets in the script:"}]},{"code":["# On the host: create a config directory","mkdir -p ~\/openclaw-configs\/work","cat > ~\/openclaw-configs\/work\/openclaw.json << 'EOF'","{","    \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514\",","    \"anthropicApiKey\": \"sk-ant-your-key-here\"","}","EOF","","# Create VM with shared folder","spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --share ~\/openclaw-configs\/work:config:ro \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the setup script, copy the config from the shared folder:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["# Inside setup-openclaw.sh","mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/openclaw.json","openclaw config validate"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"anchor":"Kubernetes-OpenClaw-Fleet","text":"Kubernetes: OpenClaw Fleet","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Deploy OpenClaw instances across multiple Macs using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the Kubernetes operator:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.io\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVMPool","metadata:","  name: openclaw-agents","  namespace: ai","spec:","  replicas: 2","  image: ghcr.io\/spooktacular\/macos:15.4","","  provisioning:","    mode: disk-inject","    userData: |","      #!\/bin\/bash","      brew install node@24","      export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","      npm install -g openclaw@latest","      mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","      # Config injected via K8s secret → shared folder","      cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/","      openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","  resources:","    cpu: 4","    memory: 8Gi","    disk: 32Gi","","  network:","    mode: nat"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"yaml"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each Mac in the fleet runs 2 OpenClaw VMs. Ten Macs ="},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"20 OpenClaw instances."}]},{"anchor":"Networking-Between-Instances","text":"Networking Between Instances","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your OpenClaw instances need to communicate (e.g.,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a coordinator agent delegating to worker agents):"}]},{"code":["spook create openclaw-coordinator --from-ipsw latest --network host-only","spook create openclaw-worker --from-ipsw latest --network host-only"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Host-only networking lets the VMs talk to each other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and to the host Mac, but not to the internet. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinator can reach the worker’s gateway at its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"host-only IP on port 18789.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For internet access + inter-VM communication, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking — both VMs can reach each other via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their NAT-assigned IPs."}]},{"anchor":"Resource-Planning","text":"Resource Planning","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CPU"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Memory"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disk"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Notes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud models only"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"4 cores","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"4 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimal — OpenClaw is lightweight"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cloud + light local models","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"4 cores","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"8 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"32 GB","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ollama with small models","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Heavy local models (Llama 3)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"6 cores","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"64 GB"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Needs unified memory"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since macOS VMs share the host’s unified memory via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Virtualization framework, the GPU (Metal) is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"available inside the VM for local model inference."}]},{"anchor":"Monitoring","text":"Monitoring","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check OpenClaw health in each VM:"}]},{"code":["# From the host","spook ssh openclaw-work -- \"openclaw status\"","spook ssh openclaw-personal -- \"openclaw status\"","","# Or via the gateway API","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-work):18789\/health","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-personal):18789\/health"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"anchor":"Snapshots","text":"Snapshots","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Save a working OpenClaw configuration before making changes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The VM must be stopped to take or restore a disk-level snapshot:"}]},{"code":["spook stop openclaw-work","spook snapshot openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless","# ... make changes, install new version ...","# If something breaks:","spook stop openclaw-work","spook restore openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"abstract":[{"text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows.","type":"text"}],"title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/NetworkMode":{"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"NetworkMode","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","abstract":[{"text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/ProvisioningMode":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/provisioningmode","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ProvisioningMode","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","title":"ProvisioningMode","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ProvisioningMode","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The strategy for executing a user-data script on a VM.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Manage macOS virtual machines from the terminal with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"}